ðŸ§± Step 1: Manual Tailwind Setup

If you already have React installed, just run:

npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p


This creates:

tailwind.config.js
postcss.config.js

ðŸ› ï¸ tailwind.config.js

Replace the generated file with this:

/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: ["./index.html", "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}"],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
};

ðŸ› ï¸ postcss.config.js

Make sure this looks like:

export default {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
};

ðŸ› ï¸ src/index.css (or main.css)

Replace everything with:

@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;


Thatâ€™s all. Tailwind will now work in your existing React project.

